The little that can be known about the history of the MS. is told us by Denis; it belonged to the famous Monastery os St. Columban at Bobbi0, from which fact it is still known as a Codex Bobiensis; then to the Convent of St. John de Carbonaria at Naples, Here Mabillon inspected it in October 1685, paying attention however only to the upper writing ¹. From Naples it was brought to Vienna in 1717, with other Mss„ by Alexander Ricardi‚ the first Librarian of the Imperial Library.
